  "instructions": [
    "Heat oil in a large Dutch oven over medium heat.",
    "Add the lamb and cook until browned on all sides, about 5 minutes.",
    "Add the onion, carrots, and potatoes, and cook until the vegetables are tender, about 10 minutes.",
    "Add the dried summer savoury leaves, garlic, lamb broth, tomato paste, salt, and pepper, and stir to combine.",
    "Bring the stew to a boil, then reduce the heat to low and simmer, covered, for 1 1/2 hours.",
    "Serve hot, garnished with fresh herbs if desired.",
    "Let the stew cool, then refrigerate or freeze for later use.",
    "Reheat the stew over low heat, stirring occasionally, until warmed through."
